sql:
SELECT model_name 
FROM models 
ORDER BY model_name;

SELECT COUNT(config_id) AS config_count
FROM model_configs
WHERE model_id = 0;

SELECT parameter_name
FROM config_hyperparameters
WHERE config_id = 0;

SELECT config_name, config_description
FROM training_configs
WHERE training_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Users and models are the core entities being tracked in this system; 
- Access types (e.g., view, download) indicate the nature of user interaction with the models; 
- Model versions are time-stamped, allowing for tracking of changes and updates; 
- Hyperparameters are key-value pairs that define the configuration of a model version; 
- The report is designed to provide insights into user behavior and model usage patterns.

